{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":59526,"duration_api_ms":97856,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6fb27edd-4b94-4701-8ef7-a63e150d5085","total_cost_usd":0.3316307499999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":754,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22784,"cache_read_input_tokens":74817,"output_tokens":1730,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":22784,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":116,"outputTokens":4624,"cacheReadInputTokens":350250,"cacheCreationInputTokens":37233,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.10480225000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":754,"outputTokens":1730,"cacheReadInputTokens":74817,"cacheCreationInputTokens":22784,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.22682850000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All three amendments are verified and accepted. The first is a simple dead-code cleanup. The second and third identify real correctness bugs in runless retry disambiguation and same-bead overlapping attempt handling, respectively, both confirmed by reading the relevant code paths.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-17-bcf4f863","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in model.rs:21-34. The `normalized.starts_with('.')` check on line 25 subsumes both `normalized == \".\"` and `normalized == \"..\"` since both strings start with '.'. The short-circuit evaluation of the `||` chain means lines 26-27 are unreachable dead code. Removing them is correct and eliminates confusion about whether there's a semantic difference between the broader and narrower checks."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-d6be598b","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified both claims. In service.rs:476 the parameter is `_started_at: DateTime<Utc>` (underscore-prefixed, intentionally unused) and is never passed to `update_task_run`. In fs.rs:2873-3022 the runless path filters `matching_indices` solely by `(bead_id, project_id)`. When the same project is reused for a second runless attempt and both reach terminal state, `record_bead_completion` replay finds multiple matches and errors with 'ambiguous task run update ... provide run_id to disambiguate'. This breaks the idempotent repair guarantee. Either `started_at` must participate in disambiguation, or the API must reject same-project runless retries."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-c776961e","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified both claims. In fs.rs:2770-2779 the guard `active.as_str() != bead_id` only rejects a *different* active bead, so bead-1/project-2/run-2 can start while bead-1/project-1/run-1 is still Running. In service.rs:168-169, `latest_task_runs_per_bead` collapses to a single entry per bead (model.rs:382-402 uses a BTreeMap keyed by bead_id, keeping only the most recent). Once run-2 reaches a terminal state, the snapshot sees in_progress_beads=0 even though run-1 is still Running in lineage. The start path must either reject or explicitly supersede the older running attempt to keep snapshot state consistent with lineage."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a2ce63b7-faf1-4bc5-8104-e8239e89b589"}
